description: Golden Earring - The Devil Made Us Do It (35 years-27 clips) [2002] DVD9 Golden Earring is a Dutch rock band, founded in 1961 in The Hague. They achieved worldwide fame with their international hit songs "Radar Love" in 1973, "Twilight Zone" in 1982, and "When the Lady Smiles" in 1984. The band's lineup consists of co-founders Rinus Gerritsen (bass and keyboards) and George Kooymans (vocals and guitar), along with Barry Hay (vocals, guitar, flute and saxophone), and Cesar Zuiderwijk (drums and percussion).
